02/10/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- President Abdullah Gul said in his opening speech to parliament on Monday (October 1st) that he hopes the Grand Assembly will be a parliament of the 21st century and will combine its responsibility to the public with its responsibilities to the world. 
In his speech, he stressed that secular principles and the supremacy of law are fundamental.
In other news Monday, Chief of Staff General Yasar Buyukanit opened the new academic year with a speech at the Military Academy in Istanbul. 
He said no one has the power to change the secular character and the principles of the republic founded by Ataturk. 
(Zaman, Radikal, Milliyet, Sabah, Hurriyet, Turkish daily news - 02/10/07; Zaman - 01/10/07)
